            <title>[HBASE-17043] parallelize select() work in mob compaction</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-17043</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Today in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hbase/blob/master/hbase-server/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/mob/compactions/PartitionedMobCompactor.java#L141&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/hbase/blob/master/hbase-server/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/mob/compactions/PartitionedMobCompactor.java#L141&lt;/a&gt;,  the select() is single-threaded. Give a large number of files, it will take several seconds to finish the job. Will see how this work can be divided and speed up the processing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
